author: Messenger Post sports@messengerpostmedia.com
title: AREA ROUNDUP: Mynderse ends season on high note
text: Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:56 PM By Messenger Post Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:56 PM Canandaigua, N.Y. SENECA FALLS — The Mynderse football team ended its season with a 43-8 win over Marcus Whitman in the Class C Connors and Ferris Bowl on Thursday. The Blue Devils outscored the Wildcats 35-0 in the first three quarters of the game. The players’ names for Mynderse were not provided. Marcus Whitman’s Ben Ayres was five for eight with 71 passing yards and Eric Link scored the lone touchdown of the game for the Wildcats on a two-yard run. Dylan Howell led the team with 27 rushing yards, while teammate Tyler CUmmings ran for 21 yards. Receiver Gavin McCumiskey made a couple of big plays for the offense, as he finished with three catches for 70 yards. McCumiskey also led the defense with eight tackles and a sack. In other high school sports action on Thursday: GIRLS VOLLEYBALL Lyons 3, Gananda 1 The Lions beat the Blue Panthers 25-23, 26-24 and 25-15. The only loss was 25-9 in the second game. Kiki Juliano led Lyons with 12 assists and two aces, while Teaonna Jenkins added six kills and five digs. Lyons improves to 13-7 and Gananda drops to 12-6 overall. Penn Yan 3, Waterloo 1 The Mustangs beat the Indians 25-21, 25-19 and 29-27. Kelly Bray led Penn Yan with 23 assists and 10 digs and Emily Wunder added 15 kills, nine digs, three aces and four blocks. The Mustangs finished the season with a 10-2 league record and as co-league champs for the first time since 1986. Waterloo’s Aubrey O’Brien had 34 digs and Brittanie Forde added 23 digs and eight kills. WEDNESDAY’S LATE RESULTS CLASS C2 No. 4 South Seneca/Romulus 6, No. 13 Cuba-Rushford 0 SS/R scored four first half goals to defeat Cuba-Rushford on Wednesday. Eli Corning scored two goals and Adam Wagner added two assists. By Messenger Post
